nd also incorporates the findings of numerous local and regional studies undertaken by German scholars. While its main focus is on the German Federal Republic, the book also provides coverage of the refugee problem in the German Democratic Republic.This accessible book on a key aspect of post-war German history will be of particular interest to undergraduates of history, politics and German.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aRefugeeszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aRefugeeszGermanyxSocial conditionsy20th century. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aGerman Federal Republic.  aGerman expellees.  aGerman refugees.  aSecond World War.  aWestern Occupation Zones.  aearly post-war years.  aeconomic integration.  aexpellee trek associations.  anewcomers' voting behaviour.  apolitical integration.  apolitical parties.  apolitical radicalisation.  apost-war Germany.  arefugee expulsion.  asocial integration.1 aConnor, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129802/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013